WALANG BASAGAN NG THRIFT
Project Documentation

1. Project Overview
Walang Basagan ng Thrift is a Y2K-inspired thrift store web application built with React, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, and an Express backend. The project combines an online storefront, role-based authentication, a shopping flow, customer support, and an admin dashboard for managing users, products, orders, homepage content, and support tickets.

The application is designed to showcase both frontend and full-stack development skills for a portfolio. It features a modern responsive UI, reusable components, data-driven content, file uploads, user roles, and local development scripts for Windows.

2. Project Goals
- Build a visually distinct thrift shop website with a Y2K aesthetic.
- Provide a smooth shopping experience for buyers.
- Separate customer, moderator, and admin capabilities.
- Include an admin dashboard for real management workflows.
- Support both SQLite and JSON-based backend storage.
- Make the project easy to run on Windows.

