- src/pages/: route-level pages such as auth, admin, support, and info pages
- src/data/: structured JSON content used by the UI

Backend:
- server/index.js: Express application and route definitions
- server/db.js: SQLite database access
- server/db-json.js: JSON storage fallback
- server/seed-admin.js: admin seed script for SQLite
- server/seed-admin-json.js: admin seed script for JSON mode
- server/seed-users.js: sample users for SQLite
- server/seed-users-json.js: sample users for JSON mode
- server/data/: backend data files
- server/uploads/: uploaded images and media

8. Routing and Navigation
The frontend uses React Router for page navigation. Common routes include:
- / : home page
- /products : product listing
- /products/:id : product details
- /cart : shopping cart
- /checkout : checkout flow
- /orders : buyer order history
- /login and /signup : authentication pages
- /admin/* : admin dashboard routes
- /info/:slug : informational pages

The app also handles conditional redirects:
- Admin and moderator accounts are sent to the dashboard after login.
- Buyers can access cart, checkout, and orders.
- Unauthenticated users are redirected to login for protected pages.

